{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:28:42.146135+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Based on the repository contents, here's a summary of how to work with this Vue 3 admin app locally and in staging/production:\n\n---\n\n## Starting Locally\n\n```bash\n# 1. Install pnpm globally\nnpm i -g pnpm\n\n# 2. Install dependencies\npnpm install\n\n# 3. Start the dev server\npnpm dev\n```\n\nThe app will open automatically at **http://localhost:9528**. The dev environment uses the `.env.development` config, which points the base API to `/dev-api`.\n\n---\n\n## Building for Staging\n\n```bash\npnpm build:stage\n```\n\nThis runs `vue-cli-service build --mode staging`, which loads `.env.staging`. In this mode, `NODE_ENV` is set to `production` (for optimal bundling), the custom `ENV` flag is set to `staging`, and the base API is pointed at `/stage-api`.\n\n---\n\n## Building for Production\n\n```bash\npnpm build:prod\n```\n\nThis runs `vue-cli-service build` with default production mode, loading `.env.production`. The base API is `/prod-api` and `ENV` is `production`.\n\n---\n\n## Previewing a Build\n\n```bash\n# Preview the production build locally\npnpm preview\n\n# Preview with static resource size analysis\npnpm preview -- --report\n```\n\nThis runs `node build/index.js --preview`, which serves the output from the `build/` directory so you can see what the built app looks like before deploying.\n\n---\n\n### Quick Reference\n\n| Task | Command |\n|---|---|\n| Local dev server | `pnpm dev` |\n| Build for staging | `pnpm build:stage` |\n| Build for production | `pnpm build:prod` |\n| Preview last build | `pnpm preview` |\n| Lint & auto-fix | `pnpm lint -- --fix` |\n\nThe package manager is **pnpm**, and the project is a **Vue 3 + Element Plus** admin template built with **Vue CLI**.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 455, "prompt_tokens": 6689, "total_tokens": 7144, "completion_token